            <div class="blurb">
    <p>I do programming languages and computer architecture.
I like research that breaks down abstraction barriers and rethinks the hardware&ndash;software interface.
I worked on <a href="research.html#approximate-computing"><em>approximate computing</em></a>, the idea that computers can be more efficient if we let them make mistakes.
See what&rsquo;s going on in <a href="https://capra.cs.cornell.edu">my research group</a>, which is called <em>Capra</em>.</p>

<p>I am an associate professor in the <a href="http://www.cs.cornell.edu/">Department of Computer Science</a> at <a href="http://www.cornell.edu/">Cornell University</a>, where I am part of the <a href="http://www.csl.cornell.edu">Computer Systems Laboratory</a> and the <a href="http://pl.cs.cornell.edu">programming languages group</a>.
I graduated from the <a href="http://www.cs.washington.edu/">University of Washington</a> in 2015.
Here&rsquo;s my <a href="/~asampson/cv/">CV</a>.</p>


