    <h3>
        <a href="/~asampson/blog/gator.html">Geometry Bugs and Geometry Types</a>
    </h3>
    <div class="excerpt">
        <p>A special kind of bug exists in code that has to deal with geometric concepts like positions, directions, coordinate systems, and all that.
Long ago, in <a href="https://dl.acm.org/doi/10.1145/3428241">an OOPSLA 2020 paper</a>, we defined <em>geometry bugs</em> and designed a <a href="https://github.com/cucapra/gator">type system</a> to catch them.
This post demonstrates the idea through some buggy <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Games/Techniques/3D_on_the_web/GLSL_Shaders">GLSL</a> shaders.</p>


